---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "search"
description: "Semantic landmark element for search functionality. Wraps search forms and controls to provide accessibility and structural meaning."
elementName: search
category: native
nativeGroup: Sectioning
currentPath: /docs/elements/native/search/
permalink: /docs/elements/native/search/
---

{% set simpleSearchCode %}<search>
  <input type="search" placeholder="Search..."
         aria-label="Search" />
</search>{% endset %}

{% set searchWithFormCode %}<search>
  <form action="/search" method="get">
    <label for="site-search" class="visually-hidden">Search</label>
    <input type="search" id="site-search" name="q"
           placeholder="Search..." />
    <button type="submit">Search</button>
  </form>
</search>{% endset %}

{% set inlineSearchCode %}<search class="inline">
  <input type="search" placeholder="Search..."
         aria-label="Search" />
  <button type="submit">Search</button>
</search>{% endset %}

{% set compactSearchCode %}<search class="compact inline">
  <input type="search" placeholder="Quick search..."
         aria-label="Search" />
  <button type="submit">Find</button>
</search>{% endset %}

{% set roundedSearchCode %}<search class="inline rounded">
  <input type="search" placeholder="Search..."
         aria-label="Search" />
  <button type="submit">Go</button>
</search>{% endset %}

{% set expandedSearchCode %}<search class="expanded">
  <input type="search"
         placeholder="Search the entire site..."
         aria-label="Search" />
</search>{% endset %}

{% set headerSearchCode %}<search class="header inline">
  <input type="search" placeholder="Search..."
         aria-label="Search" />
  <button type="submit" class="small">Go</button>
</search>{% endset %}

{% set cssImplementationCode %}search {
  display: block;
}

/* Inline variant */
search.inline {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--size-xs);

  & > input { flex: 1; }
}

/* Expanded variant */
search.expanded {
  inline-size: 100%;

  & > input { inline-size: 100%; }
}

/* Compact variant */
search.compact {
  & > input, & > button {
    padding-block: var(--size-xs);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  }
}

/* Rounded variant */
search.rounded > input {
  border-radius: var(--radius-full);
  padding-inline: var(--size-m);
}{% endset %}

{% set getFormCode %}<search>
  <form action="/search" method="get" class="inline">
    <label for="search-products"
           class="visually-hidden">Search products</label>
    <input type="search" id="search-products" name="q"
           placeholder="Search products..." />
    <button type="submit">Search</button>
  </form>
</search>{% endset %}

{% set clientFilterCode %}<search>
  <input type="search"
         placeholder="Filter results..."
         aria-label="Filter results"
         id="filter-input" />
</search>

<script>
  const input = document.getElementById('filter-input');
  input.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
    filterContent(e.target.value);
  });
</script>{% endset %}

{% set labelingExamplesCode %}<!-- Visible label -->
<label for="search">Search</label>
<input type="search" id="search" />

<!-- Hidden label (visible to screen readers) -->
<label for="search" class="visually-hidden">Search</label>
<input type="search" id="search" />

<!-- aria-label (no visible label element) -->
<input type="search" aria-label="Search" />{% endset %}

{% set multipleSearchCode %}<!-- Main site search -->
<search aria-label="Site search">
  ...
</search>

<!-- Table filter -->
<search aria-label="Filter table results">
  ...
</search>{% endset %}

  <section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;search&gt;</code> element is a semantic landmark that identifies content related to searching or filtering. It's the recommended way to mark up search functionality, replacing the older pattern of <code>&lt;form role="search"&gt;</code>.</p>
    <p>As a landmark element, <code>&lt;search&gt;</code> allows screen reader users to quickly navigate to search functionality using landmark navigation.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Site-wide search:</strong> Main search functionality in headers</li>
      <li><strong>Page search:</strong> Search within specific content (tables, lists)</li>
      <li><strong>Filter controls:</strong> Filter interfaces that narrow displayed content</li>
      <li><strong>Search results pages:</strong> Wrap the search input on results pages</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When Not to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>For login forms - use <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> with appropriate labels</li>
      <li>For general data input - use standard form elements</li>
      <li>Multiple search landmarks on one page (generally use only one)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
